.TH "WEBGL_lose_context.loseContext" "JS" "July 7, 2023" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
WEBGL_lose_context.loseContext \- WEBGL_lose_context: loseContext()
method
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]WEBGL_lose_context.loseContext()\f[R] method is part of the
WebGL API and allows you to simulate losing the context of a
\f[CR]WebGLRenderingContext\f[R] context.
.PP
It triggers the steps described in the WebGL specification for handling
context lost.
The context will remain lost until
\f[CR]WEBGL_lose_context.restoreContext()\f[R] is called.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
loseContext()
.EE
.SS Parameters
None.
.SS Return value
None (\f[CR]undefined\f[R]).
.SH EXAMPLES
With this method, you can simulate the \f[CR]webglcontextlost\f[R]
event:
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] canvas = document.getElementById(\[dq]canvas\[dq]);
\f[B]const\f[R] gl = canvas.getContext(\[dq]webgl\[dq]);

canvas.addEventListener(
  \[dq]webglcontextlost\[dq],
  (e) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
    console.log(e);
  },
  \f[B]false\f[R],
);

gl.getExtension(\[dq]WEBGL_lose_context\[dq]).loseContext();

\f[I]// WebGLContextEvent event with type \[dq]webglcontextlost\[dq] is logged.\f[R]
.EE
